with Jiang Ting's statement.

107
00:06:16,310 --> 00:06:17,750
You're in charge here, right?

108
00:06:17,750 --> 00:06:18,680
When will you police

109
00:06:18,680 --> 00:06:19,830
-ever...
-Ma'am.

110
00:06:20,070 --> 00:06:21,310
-We are prosecutors…
-My house…

111
00:06:21,310 --> 00:06:22,170
Not the police.

112
00:06:23,190 --> 00:06:24,450
Ma'am, let me explain.

113
00:06:24,680 --> 00:06:26,190
Usually after a criminal case occurs,

114
00:06:26,190 --> 00:06:27,920
once the police
complete their investigation,

115
00:06:27,920 --> 00:06:29,430
they'll transfer the case to us.

116
00:06:29,430 --> 00:06:30,920
After reviewing the case details

117
00:06:30,920 --> 00:06:32,800
and evidence,

118
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:34,190
if we believe it adds up to a crime,

119
00:06:34,190 --> 00:06:36,040
we'll press charges according to the law.

120
00:06:36,040 --> 00:06:36,950
How could we

121
00:06:37,120 --> 00:06:39,310
have rented our house to a murderer?

122
00:06:39,650 --> 00:06:41,360
Who could have seen this coming?

123
00:06:41,360 --> 00:06:42,720
She looked so frail,

124
00:06:42,740 --> 00:06:44,340
and she was with a child, too.

125
00:06:44,720 --> 00:06:45,720
She stabbed seven or eight times.

126
00:06:45,720 --> 00:06:47,250
That's incredibly brutal.

127
00:06:47,830 --> 00:06:50,159
She even hung laundry after stabbing him.

128
00:06:50,430 --> 00:06:51,830
After this, my house will be...

129
00:06:51,830 --> 00:06:53,500
Ma'am, please don't worry.

130
00:06:53,720 --> 00:06:55,390
Whether Jiang Ting is a murderer

131
00:06:55,390 --> 00:06:56,680
isn't for you to decide,

132
00:06:56,680 --> 00:06:58,280
but for the law to determine.

133
00:07:01,680 --> 00:07:03,080
Wuyan Third High School.

134
00:07:05,750 --> 00:07:07,150
Zhang Yuan and Jiang Ting

135
00:07:07,240 --> 00:07:09,770
both graduated from
Wuyan Third High School.

136
00:07:10,650 --> 00:07:12,480
They graduated from Third High School,

137
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:14,540
yet their lives turned out so poorly.

138
00:07:23,190 --> 00:07:24,000
Shaolan,

139
00:07:24,800 --> 00:07:26,400
which school did you attend?

140
00:07:26,430 --> 00:07:28,790
Is that relevant to this case?

141
00:07:28,810 --> 00:07:30,070
Maybe yes,

142
00:07:31,310 --> 00:07:32,470
maybe no.

143
00:07:38,480 --> 00:07:40,000
"The madman charges eastward."

144
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:41,750
Those who chase him also go east.

145
00:07:41,750 --> 00:07:43,480
They're in the same direction,

146
00:07:44,040 --> 00:07:45,840
but the intention is different.

147
00:07:47,760 --> 00:07:48,890
What does that mean?

148
00:07:52,820 --> 00:07:56,510
[Wuyan Municiple Detention Center]

149
00:07:56,590 --> 00:08:00,160
[Positive Mindset, Education & Guidance]

150
00:08:00,160 --> 00:08:01,680
Let's stick to our usual rule:

151
00:08:01,680 --> 00:08:03,410
Don't bring in your own stance.

152
00:08:05,240 --> 00:08:07,240
I think it was justifiable defense.

153
00:08:07,240 --> 00:08:09,300
I think it was intentional homicide.

154
00:08:09,500 --> 00:08:09,750
[Positive Mindset, Education & Guidance]

155
00:08:09,750 --> 00:08:11,010
Director Duan is here.

156
00:08:12,500 --> 00:08:14,100
Let's put that aside for now.

157
00:08:14,370 --> 00:08:20,250
[People-Centered, Genuine Support]

158
00:08:27,160 --> 00:08:27,950
Jiang Ting.

159
00:08:30,310 --> 00:08:32,110
How much did you hate Zhang Yuan?

160
00:08:32,559 --> 00:08:34,760
Why did you stab him seven times in a row?

161
00:08:35,510 --> 00:08:36,549
After you stabbed him the first time,

162
00:08:36,549 --> 00:08:38,669
he should have been unable to resist.

163
00:08:39,120 --> 00:08:40,850
Why did you stab six more times?

164
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:06,240
I don't know why I did that.

165
00:09:07,390 --> 00:09:09,000
The police don't lie,

166
00:09:10,910 --> 00:09:12,320
so it must be true.

167
00:09:14,360 --> 00:09:16,440
I wish I only stabbed him once.

168
00:09:19,200 --> 00:09:20,790
If I only stabbed once,

169
00:09:22,630 --> 00:09:25,320
what I did would be considered
a justifiable defense.

170
00:09:25,320 --> 00:09:26,120
Right?

171
00:09:28,630 --> 00:09:30,160
What if he survived my stab,

172
00:09:31,840 --> 00:09:33,500
got up, and killed me instead?

173
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:38,600
After such a serious incident,

174
00:09:38,600 --> 00:09:40,360
you called the ambulance

175
00:09:40,440 --> 00:09:42,040
and the police immediately.

176
00:09:42,390 --> 00:09:43,670
While you were waiting,

177
00:09:43,670 --> 00:09:45,630
why did you hang the clothes
washed in the washing machine

178
00:09:45,630 --> 00:09:46,790
on the balcony?

179
00:09:48,720 --> 00:09:51,200
It takes 28 minutes to wash the laundry.

180
00:09:52,200 --> 00:09:54,750
In those 28 minutes,

181
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:57,030
my life

182
00:09:57,510 --> 00:09:58,960
suddenly derailed

183
00:10:00,510 --> 00:10:02,030
and crashed into the mud.

184
00:10:04,750 --> 00:10:05,670
At that moment,

185
00:10:07,270 --> 00:10:09,750
I just wanted to hang the clothes to dry.

186
00:10:11,790 --> 00:10:13,320
When the clothes are clean,

187
00:10:14,960 --> 00:10:16,150
my life

188
00:10:17,750 --> 00:10:19,670
can go back to the past, too.

189
00:10:29,390 --> 00:10:31,320
I've read the previous statement.

190
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:33,060
You mentioned that

191
00:10:34,840 --> 00:10:37,700
Zhang Yuan thought
the dinner wasn't cooked by you.

192
00:10:38,030 --> 00:10:39,230
Why would he say that?

193
00:10:41,790 --> 00:10:42,870
He said

194
00:10:43,910 --> 00:10:46,240
I never peeled asparagus when I cooked it.

195
00:10:46,870 --> 00:10:49,200
Before Zhang Yuan barged into your house,

196
00:10:49,360 --> 00:10:50,890
had anyone else been there?

197
00:10:57,630 --> 00:10:58,480
No.

198
00:10:59,120 --> 00:11:01,120
Did you forget something again?

199
00:11:09,600 --> 00:11:10,860
Who are you expecting?

200
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:13,720
No one.

201
00:11:22,790 --> 00:11:24,920
At that moment, I was totally shocked.

202
00:11:27,440 --> 00:11:28,150
Sit.

203
00:11:28,630 --> 00:11:30,430
Why are you just standing there?

204
00:11:30,440 --> 00:11:31,240
Sit down.

205
00:11:31,270 --> 00:11:32,730
I need to hang the laundry.

206
00:11:39,750 --> 00:11:41,080
Someone came by, right?

207
00:11:42,030 --> 00:11:43,630
Whether anyone came by or not

208
00:11:44,550 --> 00:11:46,680
has nothing to do with you, doesn't it?

209
00:11:48,600 --> 00:11:50,000
Now, you talk back.

210
00:11:54,790 --> 00:11:56,200
You promised me.

211
00:11:56,320 --> 00:11:58,550
You'll keep your promise, right?

212
00:12:13,720 --> 00:12:14,550
Zhang Yuan,

213
00:12:16,270 --> 00:12:18,530
we've known each other for so many years.

214
00:12:20,080 --> 00:12:22,320
Can't we just part on good terms?

215
00:12:26,550 --> 00:12:28,280
When did you learn to keep fish?

216
00:12:30,320 --> 00:12:31,580
They're from a friend.

217
00:12:33,550 --> 00:12:34,600
Which friend?

218
00:12:38,150 --> 00:12:39,440
Someone you don't know.

219
00:12:39,440 --> 00:12:40,360
A new friend?

220
00:12:41,240 --> 00:12:42,120
Call him over.

221
00:12:42,240 --> 00:12:44,840
Have dinner together,
and I'll get to know him.

222
00:12:55,750 --> 00:12:57,350
The asparagus is delicious.

223
00:12:58,960 --> 00:13:00,820
Pity that it's not you who made it.

224
00:13:02,360 --> 00:13:04,870
You never peel the asparagus.

225
00:13:11,840 --> 00:13:13,550
Come here. Eat with me.

226
00:13:18,480 --> 00:13:19,840
I told you to come here!

227
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:30,800
Zhang Yuan was always paranoid.

228
00:13:31,440 --> 00:13:32,870
Even if he saw a rooster,

229
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:35,030
he'd think I'd cheat on him with it.

230
00:13:36,240 --> 00:13:37,550
If he wanted to hit me,

231
00:13:38,030 --> 00:13:39,690
anything could be his excuse.

232
00:13:43,360 --> 00:13:44,560
Come here. Come here.

233
00:13:45,510 --> 00:13:46,200
Yes.

234
00:13:47,480 --> 00:13:49,610
I just want to have a good meal with you.

235
00:13:50,030 --> 00:13:50,630
Here.

236
00:13:52,390 --> 00:13:54,050
You haven't eaten yet, right?

237
00:13:54,910 --> 00:13:57,120
Come on. Try it. See if it's good.

238
00:13:57,750 --> 00:13:59,240
Have you tried his cooking?

239
00:13:59,240 --> 00:14:00,300
Have a taste.

240
00:14:00,360 --> 00:14:01,870
Come on. Try it.

241
00:14:02,390 --> 00:14:04,120
Haven't you tried his cooking?

242
00:14:04,150 --> 00:14:05,120
Have a bite.

243
00:14:05,390 --> 00:14:06,870
You tart!

244
00:14:08,150 --> 00:14:09,750
You're with a man behind my back,
aren't you?

245
00:14:09,750 --> 00:14:11,550
I'll kill you if you come closer!

246
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:13,800
You dare to hold a knife now, huh?

247
00:14:14,270 --> 00:14:15,200
Run!

248
00:14:19,720 --> 00:14:20,550
Kill me then!

249
00:14:29,750 --> 00:14:30,680
Don't come over.

250
00:14:33,390 --> 00:14:34,120
Murder.

251
00:14:35,200 --> 00:14:36,270
Please...

252
00:14:39,440 --> 00:14:40,000
Come on.

253
00:14:40,840 --> 00:14:42,510
Today I'm going to kill you!

254
00:14:52,670 --> 00:14:54,150
You dare stab me?

255
00:15:23,790 --> 00:15:26,250
The legal provision on justifiable defense

256
00:15:27,510 --> 00:15:29,480
is just a few short lines.

257
00:15:30,670 --> 00:15:32,000
The law seems clear,

258
00:15:33,840 --> 00:15:36,700
but the more I read it,
the more complicated it gets,

259
00:15:37,030 --> 00:15:38,630
and the less I understand it.

260
00:15:39,200 --> 00:15:40,240
I know less

261
00:15:41,240 --> 00:15:42,870
what crime I'm guilty of now.

262
00:15:45,360 --> 00:15:47,360
I couldn't hold onto my past,

263
00:15:50,270 --> 00:15:52,330
and now I can't see my future clearly.

264
00:15:55,910 --> 00:15:58,150
You can convict me of murder

265
00:15:59,120 --> 00:16:00,670
and put me behind bars.

266
00:16:05,120 --> 00:16:06,000
That's okay.

267
00:16:08,630 --> 00:16:10,320
But can anyone tell me,

268
00:16:11,840 --> 00:16:13,750
in that situation,

269
00:16:14,510 --> 00:16:15,840
if I hadn't fought back,

270
00:16:17,910 --> 00:16:19,440
what else could I have done?

271
00:16:21,080 --> 00:16:23,000
My mom is taking care of my child.

272
00:16:23,960 --> 00:16:25,670
I have nothing to worry about.

273
00:16:26,200 --> 00:16:28,170
But if no one's taking care of the fish,

274
00:16:28,170 --> 00:16:29,240
they will die.

275
00:16:30,640 --> 00:16:30,910
[The above statements are…]

276
00:16:30,910 --> 00:16:31,910
Director Duan,

277
00:16:33,240 --> 00:16:34,970
can you take care of them for me?

278
00:16:35,740 --> 00:16:36,200
[Jiang Ting]

279
00:16:36,200 --> 00:16:37,220
Or

280
00:16:38,120 --> 00:16:39,920
